of great suffering there

00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:31.350 align:middle line:90%
for many people.

00:02:31.350 --> 00:02:35.720 align:middle line:84%
Why is it that there's so much
conflict in relationships?

00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:37.560 align:middle line:90%
And does it have to be that way?

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:43.100 align:middle line:84%
So we need to look at what the
source of that conflict may be.

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:47.480 align:middle line:84%
Now most people
experience periodic drama

00:02:47.480 --> 00:02:53.120 align:middle line:84%
in their relationships, once
a week, every other day,

00:02:53.120 --> 00:02:55.700 align:middle line:90%
depending on the relationship.

00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:59.780 align:middle line:84%
>> And we can become addicted to
the drama itself because it is

00:02:59.780 --> 00:03:03.110 align:middle line:84%
emotional, it is intense,
and we experience it.

00:03:03.110 --> 00:03:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And even if it's
painful, it's intense.

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:10.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, there is something
that one could almost call

00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:15.260 align:middle line:84%
an addiction to suffering
in most human beings,

00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:18.620 align:middle line:84%
but that's mostly unconscious
or they don't know that they are

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:20.510 align:middle line:90%
addicted to suffering.

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:24.160 align:middle line:84%
And what that is is
not so much caused--

00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:27.050 align:middle line:84%
it seemingly caused
by the relationship,

00:03:27.050 --> 00:03:32.060 align:middle line:84%
but the fact is that human
beings over thousands

00:03:32.060 --> 00:03:34.520 align:middle line:84%
of years of history
have created so much

00:03:34.520 --> 00:03:36.260 align:middle line:90%
suffering for themselves.

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:37.850 align:middle line:84%
If you look at
human history, you

00:03:37.850 --> 00:03:42.200 align:middle line:84%
see the atrocities,
almost continuous warfare

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:43.700 align:middle line:90%
that's been going on.

00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:51.020 align:middle line:84%
So that has left traces in the
human collective consciousness,

00:03:51.020 --> 00:03:57.410 align:middle line:84%
and those are residues
of past human suffering.

00:03:57.410 --> 00:04:00.620 align:middle line:84%
Even the planet itself
carries an energy

00:04:00.620 --> 00:04:05.690 align:middle line:84%
field of suffering collectively
in a collective psyche.

00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:09.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Through all these generations
and ancestors we've known.

00:04:09.350 --> 00:04:12.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, and I call
that the pain body.

00:04:12.260 --> 00:04:16.850 align:middle line:84%
So it's a residue of
past emotional suffering,

00:04:16.850 --> 00:04:21.019 align:middle line:84%
both the past of humanity
and your own personal past

00:04:21.019 --> 00:04:25.160 align:middle line:84%
because every child suffers
in one way or another.

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:28.900 align:middle line:84%
So all the emotional
suffering that you go to

00:04:28.900 --> 00:04:33.470 align:middle line:84%
is added to the pain
body, the emotional sphere

00:04:33.470 --> 00:04:38.000 align:middle line:84%
of suffering that you've already
come into this world with.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:39.510 align:middle line:90%
So this pain body--

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:42.110 align:middle line:84%
now I'm going to look
at it for a moment

00:04:42.110 --> 00:04:45.650 align:middle line:84%
as if it were almost
an independent entity,

00:04:45.650 --> 00:04:50.360 align:middle line:84%
it's an emotional energy
field that lives in you,

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:53.570 align:middle line:84%
and the pain body is
not always active.

00:04:53.570 --> 00:04:56.510 align:middle line:84%
It has a dormant period
when you can hardly feel it

00:04:56.510 --> 00:04:58.950 align:middle line:90%
and everything seems to be fine.

00:04:58.950 --> 00:05:01.700 align:middle line:84%
And then it has an
active period when

00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:84%
it needs to come up and feed
again, add to its suffering

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:09.930 align:middle line:90%
by creating more suffering.

00:05:09.930 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
So this pain body that
people carry inside

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:17.730 align:middle line:84%
from the past, past
emotion, periodically

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:21.390 align:middle line:84%
comes out of its
dormant state and seeks

00:05:21.390 --> 00:05:23.490 align:middle line:84%
some further
experience of suffering

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:26.980 align:middle line:84%
because that is the energy
vibration that it feeds on.

00:05:26.980 --> 00:05:32.150 align:middle line:84%
So the first thing that happens,
a little trigger awakens

00:05:32.150 --> 00:05:34.320 align:middle line:84%
the pain body, something
relatively insignificant

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:35.120 align:middle line:90%
happens.

00:05:35.120 --> 00:05:36.920 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps in your
relationship, your partner

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:40.070 align:middle line:84%
says something, makes a
comment, and suddenly, there's

00:05:40.070 --> 00:05:43.070 align:middle line:84%
an enormous reaction
out of proportion

00:05:43.070 --> 00:05:46.100 align:middle line:84%
to the significance of
the triggering effect,

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:49.140 align:middle line:84%
and the pain body came up
because it needed to feed.

00:05:49.140 --> 00:05:52.670 align:middle line:84%
So the pain body
feeds into ways.

00:05:52.670 --> 00:05:57.440 align:middle line:84%
It feeds on your mind by
rising up into your thoughts

00:05:57.440 --> 00:06:01.160 align:middle line:84%
and making your thought
processes very negative.

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:03.410 align:middle line:84%
They become negative
and self-destructive,

00:06:03.410 --> 00:06:06.350 align:middle line:90%
destructive of self or others.

00:06:06.350 --> 00:06:11.030 align:middle line:84%
So every negative thought has
a certain frequency vibration

00:06:11.030 --> 00:06:15.830 align:middle line:84%
to it, which corresponds to the
emotional frequency of the pain

00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:16.970 align:middle line:90%
body.

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:20.900 align:middle line:84%
And some pain bodies are
predominantly angry pain

00:06:20.900 --> 00:06:21.770 align:middle line:90%
bodies.

00:06:21.770 --> 00:06:27.050 align:middle line:84%
Other pain bodies are
predominantly sad or extremely

00:06:27.050 --> 00:06:28.630 align:middle line:90%
turbulent or fearful.

00:06:28.630 --> 00:06:30.480 align:middle line:84%
>> But we all know
that pain body.

00:06:30.480 --> 00:06:32.897 align:middle line:84%
And we know how it can come
up, and it's disproportionate,

00:06:32.897 --> 00:06:36.170 align:middle line:84%
as you said, to what has
actually happened to us.

00:06:36.170 --> 00:06:37.970 align:middle line:84%
But we can dissolve
the pain body.

00:06:37.970 --> 00:06:40.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, now the pain
body will try to feed,

00:06:40.910 --> 00:06:42.140 align:middle line:90%
to add to its energy.

00:06:42.140 --> 00:06:44.480 align:middle line:84%
It wants you to
completely identify

00:06:44.480 --> 00:06:49.370 align:middle line:84%
with that energy field
that represents that it is,

00:06:49.370 --> 00:06:50.990 align:middle line:90%
so it will feed on your mind.

00:06:50.990 --> 00:06:53.090 align:middle line:84%
But in relationships,
it will also

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:56.840 align:middle line:84%
feed on reactions, your
partner's reactions.

00:06:56.840 --> 00:06:58.800 align:middle line:84%
It will unconsciously--
of course,

00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:01.160 align:middle line:84%
you don't know that when
you identified with it.

00:07:01.160 --> 00:07:03.440 align:middle line:84%
You don't know that this
is what you're doing.

00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:07.820 align:middle line:84%
You will try to make
your partner react

00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:10.730 align:middle line:84%
in a certain way that
feeds your pain body,

00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:14.930 align:middle line:84%
also by provoking
anger, for example.

00:07:14.930 --> 00:07:18.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's done unconsciously,
so the reaction, your partner's

00:07:18.050 --> 00:07:21.620 align:middle line:84%
reaction, will be
feeding your pain body,

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:25.670 align:middle line:84%
and that is what I call the need
for drama in a relationship.

00:07:25.670 --> 00:07:28.490 align:middle line:84%
>> You know what I like about
this too is once you think

00:07:28.490 --> 00:07:31.670 align:middle line:84%
of this pain body as
a separate entity,

00:07:31.670 --> 00:07:34.010 align:middle line:90%
that you detach from it--

00:07:34.010 --> 00:07:36.080 align:middle line:84%
and you literally then
can detach from it?

00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:40.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, when you
know it is not you,

00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:43.260 align:middle line:90%
it loses its personal nature.

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:47.810 align:middle line:84%
So, kind of, the pain that you
experience periodically then

00:07:47.810 --> 00:07:49.550 align:middle line:90%
becomes depersonalized.

00:07:49.550 --> 00:07:55.490 align:middle line:84%
It's no longer my pain, my
identity, my painful story,

00:07:55.490 --> 00:07:59.450 align:middle line:84%
but simply you know that
it is human pain that

00:07:59.450 --> 00:08:02.420 align:middle line:84%
lives in you because
there's really nothing

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:04.460 align:middle line:90%
personal about these feelings.

00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:06.800 align:middle line:90%
Anger is not a personal anger.

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:07.880 align:middle line:90%
It's human anger.

00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:11.090 align:middle line:84%
It's the same in every human
being, the same feeling.

00:08:11.090 --> 00:08:13.670 align:middle line:84%
Sadness is the same
feeling of sadness.

00:08:13.670 --> 00:08:15.410 align:middle line:90%
Fear is fear.

00:08:15.410 --> 00:08:18.030 align:middle line:10%
But people personalize
it completely,

00:08:18.030 --> 00:08:23.420 align:middle line:10%
so the emotion
energizes and amplifies

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:25.970 align:middle line:10%
the mind-made sense of
self, which then becomes

00:08:25.970 --> 00:08:28.200 align:middle line:10%
a very fearful or angry one.

00:08:28.200 --> 00:08:32.240 align:middle line:10%
>> It's mentioned that women
especially experience this

00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:35.840 align:middle line:10%
because we really
empathize with,

00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:39.964 align:middle line:10%
we have that history
of the women of Afghan,

00:08:39.964 --> 00:08:43.070 align:middle line:10%
of Afghanistan, that had to
wear the burqas and the way that

00:08:43.070 --> 00:08:45.350 align:middle line:10%
women have been tortured
and because they're smaller,

00:08:45.350 --> 00:08:47.190 align:middle line:10%
and they've been
raped and so forth.

00:08:47.190 --> 00:08:49.880 align:middle line:84%
So there is part of that is
part of this whole culture

00:08:49.880 --> 00:08:52.970 align:middle line:84%
in the whole pain
body of the race.

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:56.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, there is a collective
aspect to pain body in that

00:08:56.630 --> 00:09:02.600 align:middle line:84%
sense that certain countries
have a heavier collective pain

00:09:02.600 --> 00:09:05.180 align:middle line:84%
body in other countries, and
those tend to be countries

00:09:05.180 --> 00:09:09.380 align:middle line:84%
where many atrocities or
continuous warfare has

00:09:09.380 --> 00:09:10.180 align:middle line:90%
happened.

00:09:10.180 --> 00:09:15.430 align:middle line:84%
In Eastern Europe, if you go
to east European countries,

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:17.480 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes central
European countries,

00:09:17.480 --> 00:09:20.900 align:middle line:84%
you can often sense there's a
certain heaviness in the energy

00:09:20.900 --> 00:09:23.900 align:middle line:84%
field, and that is the
collective pain body.

00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:26.030 align:middle line:84%
Another aspect of the
collective pain body

00:09:26.030 --> 00:09:30.740 align:middle line:84%
is that certain races who
have suffered a lot also

00:09:30.740 --> 00:09:34.070 align:middle line:84%
have accumulated a stronger
collective pain body.

00:09:34.070 --> 00:09:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And women who have been victims,
really, for thousands of years

00:09:39.650 --> 00:09:43.670 align:middle line:84%
also have a collective female
pain body that I point--

00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:45.410 align:middle line:84%
I've talked about
in the book that it

00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:50.060 align:middle line:84%
tends to come up particularly
before menstruation in women,

00:09:50.060 --> 00:09:53.510 align:middle line:84%
and there's suddenly
great emotional turmoil.

00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And it can take you over so
easily when you become totally

00:09:57.500 --> 00:09:59.060 align:middle line:84%
identified with it,
and you're forced

00:09:59.060 --> 00:10:01.820 align:middle line:90%
to act it out again and again.

00:10:01.820 --> 00:10:02.750 align:middle line:90%
So how do--

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:03.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Monthly basis.

00:10:03.610 --> 00:10:04.040 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:04.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:04.940 --> 00:10:07.190 align:middle line:84%
Not that men don't
have a pain body.

00:10:07.190 --> 00:10:10.640 align:middle line:84%
They also have a pain body, but
there's the collective aspect

00:10:10.640 --> 00:10:12.540 align:middle line:90%
of the female pain body.

00:10:12.540 --> 00:10:16.190 align:middle line:84%
So once you know that,
then you can actually

00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:20.780 align:middle line:84%
bring more presence into
it and simply observe

00:10:20.780 --> 00:10:25.640 align:middle line:84%
that movement, that turbulence,
or that heaviness inside you,

00:10:25.640 --> 00:10:28.100 align:middle line:84%
so it doesn't control
your thinking anymore.

00:10:28.100 --> 00:10:33.050 align:middle line:84%
You simply feel the turbulence
or the heaviness inside you

00:10:33.050 --> 00:10:37.400 align:middle line:84%
and watch it, so you bring
a certain amount of presence

00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:41.660 align:middle line:84%
to it, and that is
bringing the power of now

00:10:41.660 --> 00:10:46.640 align:middle line:84%
into those emotions that are
part of the human pain body.

00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:50.000 align:middle line:84%
And that is the arising,
really, of a new state,

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:55.190 align:middle line:84%
a deeper, or higher state
of consciousness that is not

00:10:55.190 --> 00:11:00.140 align:middle line:84%
conditioned, that has the
ability to simply witness what

00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:01.430 align:middle line:90%
is taking place.

00:11:01.430 --> 00:11:03.440 align:middle line:84%
>> And that shifts that
whole consciousness.

00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:06.170 align:middle line:84%
>> That shifts it, and you
are no longer feeling it.

00:11:06.170 --> 00:11:08.180 align:middle line:84%
When you know that
that's what it

00:11:08.180 --> 00:11:11.810 align:middle line:84%
is, it's less likely that
the pain body can move

00:11:11.810 --> 00:11:15.620 align:middle line:84%
into your mind, force you to
think certain thoughts, which,

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:19.070 align:middle line:84%
of course, will be negative,
and it's also less likely

00:11:19.070 --> 00:11:23.300 align:middle line:84%
that the pain body will
make you use your partner

00:11:23.300 --> 00:11:28.415 align:middle line:84%
to give you more pain in its
need to reenact this drama.

00:11:28.415 --> 00:11:29.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Over and over, the drama.

